'''José Fajardo Nelson''' (born 18 August 1993) is a Panamanian [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for [[C.D. Universidad Católica del Ecuador|Universidad Catolica del Ecuador]] on loan from [[C.A. Independiente de La Chorrera|CAI]] and the [[Panama national football team|Panama national team]].<ref name="soccerway">{{cite web |url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/jose-fajardo-nelson/491588/ |title=Panama – J. Fajardo – Profile with news, career statistics and history |website=Soccerway |publisher=[[Perform Group]] |access-date=15 May 2018}}</ref>

==Club career==
Fajardo began his career with promoted side [[Independiente F.C.|Independiente]] in the [[Liga Panameña de Fútbol]] during the 2017–18 season. Fajardo finished as top scorer of the [[2017–18 Liga Panameña de Fútbol season|2018 Clausura]], leading Independiente to their first ever national league title.<ref name="soccerway"/>

==International career==
Fajardo made his international debut for [[Panama national football team|Panama]] on 25 October 2017 in a 5–0 [[Exhibition game|friendly]] away win against [[Grenada national football team|Grenada]]. On 14 May 2018, Fajardo was included in Panama's preliminary squad for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]],<ref>{{cite news |url=https://es.fifa.com/worldcup/news/panama-anuncia-su-lista-provisional-rusia-2018 |title=Panamá anuncia su lista provisional |trans-title=Panama announces its provisional list |website=FIFA.com |publisher=Fédération Internationale de Football Association |date=14 May 2018 |access-date=15 May 2018 |language=Spanish}}</ref> but was not able to make the final 23.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.espn.co.uk/football/panama/story/3513736/panamas-final-world-cup-squad-includes-six-mls-players|title = Panama's final squad includes 6 MLS players|date = 30 May 2018}}</ref> On 27 June 2024, Fajardo scored against the [[USMNT|United States]] in the [[2024 Copa America]] to win the game in the 83rd minute.

